    </exercise><exercise id="fs-id3384854" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id3025950">    <para id="import-auto-id3059568">Radio waves transmitted through space at <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>00</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>m/s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{3 "." "00" times "10" rSup { size 8{8} } "m/s"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> by the Voyager spacecraft have a wavelength of 0.120 m. What is their frequency?</para></problem></exercise>
